{{!
    @template tool_vault/start_backup

    Example context (json):
    {
        "uniqueid": "12345",
        "description": "My backup"
    }

}}

<p>Schedule backup</p>

<form>
    <p><label for="passphrase{{uniqueid}}">Passphrase</label>
    <input type="text" name="passphrase" id="passphrase{{uniqueid}}"></p>
    <p><label for="description{{uniqueid}}">Description (optional)</label>
    <textarea type="text" name="description" id="description{{uniqueid}}">{{{description}}}</textarea></p>
</form>
<p>All data will be encrypted except for: description, timestamp, size of the backup.
Your passphrase will be strored on your Moodle site until the end of this backup and after that destroyed.
    You will need to type the passphrase to restore this backup.
</p>
